page.title: 06CLUBS IN KEYINGHAM AND AREAS
page.content: There are many different clubs in this area, catering for young and old, most of these are organised and run on a self funding volantary basis and although very well supported by everyone it is not uncommon to find the same people having to do most of the organising and work involved. Some examples of these clubs are:- Cubs, Scouts, Brownies, Guides, Womens Institutes (both at Keyingham and Ottringham), Darby and Joan (for the over 60's), Football Clubs, Youth Clubs, Keep fit and Aerobics, Social Groups, Mother and Toddler Group, Playgroup, Brightour (run by the Methodist Church).
